It would be 5 stars, but I did find a long black curly hair in my lettuce that I could not pull out, so I threw out most of my lettuce. I was grossed out! ...only for 2 minutes. I had to make a decision to not let the "hair-in-my-salad" ruin my once a week of eating at a "fast food" comfort food chain. But, don't let the hair factor discourage you too much. I did talk to manager about it. I have confidence they will correct that problem. We shall see. If it were not for the hair in my salad, it would be 5 stars because the ingredients appear and taste fresh & delicious. If you consider chipotle a "fast food chain," I would consider it the Rolls Royce's of fast food: natural, fresh, hot & delicious. The seasonings in each of the items in my sofritas [?sp] (grounded tofu) vegetarian bowl were just right: sweet corn, black bean & its broth (yum), pinto beans, brown rice, teaspoon of chopped tomatoes, shredded romaine lettuce & sprinkled cheddar cheese. When all these put together, it sure taste like homemade cooking. That's why I took it to-go and brought it home, so I can add my own fresh organic chopped avocado, sprinkle with organic olive oil and organic Italian seasonings, & organic lime. Prayed over it and had an amazing moment of joy and appreciation. Life is good when you can enjoy life with little pleasures💚😋🥰
